<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,153,1331]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1196,1223]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Comments.</emphasis>
Compared with the other species that have antennal sockets on a high protruding shelf, thick, curled antennae, eyes setose, and face polished and densely punctate, the fore wing with large transverse areolet, distinctly wider than high, occiput deeply concave, face and frontal orbits fuscous, unlike in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[1223,1349,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipes">
<emphasis box="[1223,1349,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O. fuscipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; from 
<taxonomicName box="[323,450,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis box="[323,450,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in the scarce eyes setae.
</paragraph>
